content.description:
Sit start around the far right corner on the decent sloper crimp of the low ledge. Then work your way out left using heel hooks to shimmy yourself over to the far left where you will top out. The hardest part is moving around the first corner and keeping the heel on because if it pops a dab is certain.

 Beta: ​https://vimeo.com/398395988​​​
content.location: directly behind Tree Slab on the big Jim boulder in the boat landing area.

content.description: Around corner from Big Jim, climb easy slab next to tree.
content.location: Downhill from Deutschlander wall, right of Big Jim.

content.description: start on far right and climb low ledge hand over hand to the arete then top out.
content.protection: pads but its nice and low
content.location: low traverse on back side of grounded boulder

content.description: Stellar problem.  start on jugs reg. or underclings on the arete.  up to obvious sidepull match and to the top for topout.
content.location: just below cliffline faces the road

content.description: Stand start  two crimps in the middle of the face, paste your feet and hit the top.   Sit start is possible
content.protection: a pad or two, pointy rock in the landing
content.location: if you are looking at grounded for life, it is up and to the right.

content.description: Start with a good arm hook under the arete and a undercling with the left hand. Top out is tricky.
content.location: Just right of Muramasa. Up and right from Grounded for Life.

content.description:
Sit start on the low sloper with a heel-toe cam in order to grab a pretty decent crimp in the crack. Once you've gained control of the crimp bring your foot up to the big ledge then move the left hand up to an intermediate then bump to nice rail then top out. This is no ultra mega classic route by any means but definitely one id suggest hopping on if you're looking for something to do in the area. Felt easy to me but maybe harder for taller climbers.

 Send vid: ​https://vimeo.com/398395225​​​
content.location: Left of Big Jim Left in the boat landing area.

content.description: If you're facing 'Out Past Curfew' it's on your left. Start on the far left and traverse right and up. not a bad little warm up.

Crux is pulling up to the face and topping it out. Also odd at first to have the rock behind you for the traverse in. Not bad when you get used to it but kinda "inspect her gadget" at hp40 ish. but not as intrusive. cool features and good movement. Starts on obvious jug and goes to the right using the various lip holds and also the crack inside the roof for about 5 feet or so and then up the face
content.location: It is right behind "Out Past Curfew" just walk around to the right.

content.description: Start sitting with your right hand on a low undercling and left hand on a pinch on the arete, pull on and bust a hard move up and right then set feet and throw for a decent sloper higher on the arete.
content.location: This is just to the left of Out Past Curfew, on the same boulder.

climbs.name: Capitalization Separates Us From the Animals

content.description: Climbs directly through "time out". Starts on a good left hand sidepull in the wide horizontal. Good sloper on the lip and jugs to top out.
An initial low mantel move (4 feet off ground)into some very easy slab work. Fun practice and very low risk.
content.protection: A pad helps with the low start
content.location: Starts with very poor feet to the right/center, and hands on the left of the mantel. After the mantel its an easy walk up a slab, with a few cracks for hands if needed.

content.description: start on left side and move up left crack to high jug then make big move up and right to top out
start on right hold of upper crack and climb line between the two aretes.
Large boulder that faces downhill from the Deutschlander wall.  Start on jugs and cruise your way up steep prow.  Super fun!
content.location: Large boulders on slope downhill from the Deutschlander wall

content.description: start the same as grounded for life. continue to the first sloperhold this becomes a small side pull for your right hand and exit out straight up from here. fun little variation
content.location: start as for grounded for life.

content.description: It's in the trees near the boat launch just below the cliff line.
